@namespace DotNetCloud.Modules.Calendar.UI

@*
    Help content for the Calendar module.
    Based on docs/user/CALENDAR.md.
*@

<div class="help-content">
    <section class="help-section">
        <h2 class="help-section-title">Overview</h2>
        <p>DotNetCloud Calendar lets you manage calendars and events, invite attendees, set reminders, and sync with external calendar applications via CalDAV.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="help-section">
        <h2 class="help-section-title">Managing Calendars</h2>
        <p><strong>Creating a calendar:</strong> Open Calendar, click <strong>New Calendar</strong>, and enter a name. Optionally set a description, color, and timezone.</p>
        <p><strong>Editing:</strong> Click the settings icon next to a calendar name to update its details.</p>
        <p><strong>Hiding:</strong> Toggle the visibility checkbox to show or hide a calendar's events without deleting it.</p>
        <p><strong>Deleting:</strong> Click the settings icon and choose <strong>Delete</strong>. The calendar and its events are soft-deleted.</p>
        <p>You can have multiple calendars (e.g., "Work", "Personal", "Holidays").</p>
    </section>

    <section class="help-section">
        <h2 class="help-section-title">Managing Events</h2>
        <p><strong>Creating an event:</strong> Click on a date/time in the calendar view, or click <strong>New Event</strong>. Fill in the title, calendar, start/end time, location, description, and optional color override.</p>
        <p><strong>All-day events:</strong> Toggle the <strong>All Day</strong> option for full-day events.</p>
        <p><strong>Editing:</strong> Click on an event and select <strong>Edit</strong>.</p>
        <p><strong>Deleting:</strong> Click on an event and select <strong>Delete</strong>. Events are soft-deleted.</p>
        <p><strong>Searching:</strong> Use the search icon in the toolbar to find events by title, description, or location.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="help-section">
        <h2 class="help-section-title">Invitations</h2>
        <p>Add attendees to events by entering their email addresses. Attendees receive notifications and can respond (accept, decline, tentative).</p>
    </section>

    <section class="help-section">
        <h2 class="help-section-title">Reminders</h2>
        <p>Set reminders for events to receive notifications before the start time. Multiple reminders can be added per event.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="help-section">
        <h2 class="help-section-title">CalDAV Sync</h2>
        <p>Calendars are accessible via CalDAV, allowing you to sync with external applications like Thunderbird, Apple Calendar, or mobile devices. Use your DotNetCloud credentials to connect.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="help-section">
        <h2 class="help-section-title">Tips &amp; Tricks</h2>
        <ul class="help-tips">
            <li>Use different colors for different calendars for quick visual identification.</li>
            <li>Set a default reminder for all new events in your calendar settings.</li>
            <li>Share your calendar with team members to coordinate schedules.</li>
        </ul>
    </section>
</div>
